President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate five individuals to serve as United States Marshals in their respective jurisdictions. The United States Marshals play a crucial role in protecting the Federal judiciary by apprehending fugitives, transporting prisoners, and safeguarding witnesses. The nominees include Dallas L. Carlson of North Dakota for the District of North Dakota, Sonya K. Chavez of New Mexico for the District of New Mexico, Gregory Allyn Forest of North Carolina for the Western District of North Carolina, Brendan O. Heffner of Illinois for the Central District of Illinois, and Bradley A. Maxwell of Illinois for the Southern District of Illinois. Additionally, Theodor G. Short of Maine has been nominated to serve as the United States Marshal for the District of Maine. These candidates share the President's vision for "Making America Safe Again."